summary: Why does the author of this memoir choose generic topics to write about despite it’s stunning aesthetic and visual design...
body:
Why does the author of this memoir choose generic topics to write about despite it’s stunning aesthetic and visual design choices?

Why are they writing like a middle schooler who can efficiently use SAT words?

Why are they so fixated on making unnecessary reference to their appearance?

How is this guy a NYT best seller when his poetry is so average?

Oh this was written by a Youtuber…

That’s my missing context. I can now better understand this guy & not be vaguely annoyed as I continue to read. I get the random social media jokes/references now.

I was reading this as some young self involved ceo from a rich family who finally chilled out about conforming to society and their gay struggles & it was so irritating because of the generic positivity. Now that I know it’s a Youtuber the annoying superficial positivity and social media references are 100% forgivable.
